{% block lorebook %}
MONTGOMERY AL — PERMANENT CONTEXT:
- Population: ~200,000 residents, Montgomery County (FIPS 01101)
- Geography: 71 census tracts, ACS 5-year estimates available 2012-2024
- Neighborhoods are mapped to zip codes (OSM and Google Maps lack sufficient granularity for Montgomery AL)
- Data sources in this system: Census ACS (income, poverty, vacancy, unemployment, rent), Montgomery ArcGIS Open Data (code violations, building permits, fire incidents, housing conditions, food safety, environmental nuisance, transit, education, infrastructure), Yelp via Bright Data (500 businesses sampled)
- Civic categories: infrastructure, environment, housing, public_safety, transportation, health, education, economy, parks_culture, governance
- Census metrics direction: for median_income and median_rent, positive slope = improving. For poverty_below, housing_vacant, and unemployed, negative slope = improving (fewer problems).
- R² interpretation: R² >= 0.7 = reliable trend. R² 0.5-0.7 = moderate confidence. R² < 0.5 = low confidence, do not draw conclusions.
